channel.title: Need Help With One Compile Error
channel.description:
ok i get one error when i compile and i need your help to fix it.
[code]client.java:13199: 'else' without 'if' else if (NpcDialogue == 1007) { ^ 1 error Finished! Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
when i erase the 'if', i get 4 errors. plzz help!

item.title: Need Help With One Compile Error
item.dc:creator: @nklink nklink
item.description:
@nklink wrote:

I get that error sometimes too… even when my compiler is working great one second then messed up the next =[ here’s what I do. (Just to let you know you may lose everything that you coded but it’s the only way I know how to fix that problem) I re-download my source and i make a copy of the source BUT DO NOT EXTRACT THE FILE THROUGH WINRAR! Open your file with winrar remember do not extract the files… and go to your client.java… copy it all… now go to your other client.java the one with the error in it and delete it all, then paste the copy of client.java into the old messed up client file… then save and compile!

NOTE: DO NOT GET MAD AT ME IF YOU LOSE ALL OF THE STUFF YOU CODED I WARNED YOU AT THE BEGINNING OF THE TUTORIAL!
